Package: rstudio.quickwd
Title: RStudio Quick Working Directory — One Add-in (Clipboard or Active File)
Version: 2.1.0
Authors@R: person("HTang", email = "tang.heng@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: One RStudio add-in (Windows, macOS, Linux), manually triggered, that
    sets working directory and the Files pane from a clipboard path, or from the
    on-disk path of the file open in the active editor tab (parent folder).
    Each run uses the clipboard when its first line is a valid path, else the
    active tab path via 'rstudioapi'. Optional arguments force clipboard-only or
    active-tab-only. Uses 'clipr'; on Linux you may need xclip, xsel, or
    wl-clipboard.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    clipr (>= 0.4),
    rstudioapi (>= 0.13)
